lished the first Carthusian monastery in England.","Scottish and Irish: adopted as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic personal name <i>Aodh</i>, a derivative of a Gaelic word meaning ‘fire’. See   Hughes  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 邱 and 丘, based on their Hakka pronunciation; see   Qiu   1 and 2."]},{"name":"Hewes","meanings":["English (Essex):","variant of   Hughes  .","variant of   Hawes  ."]}]},{"name":"Lady","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>lavedi</i>, <i>levedi</i>, <i>ladi</i> ‘lady, female head of a household, woman, wife’ (Old English <i>hlǣfdige</i>). As a man's name it may have been used in mockery, or be short for occupational names such as <b>Ladyman</b>.","Polish: variant of   Lada  .","Hungarian (<b>Ládi</b>): habitational name for someone from Lád in Borsod County or Lad in Somogy County."],"variants":[{"name":"Lada","meanings":["‘Morning dew’; also ‘generosity’."]}]},{"name":"Frances","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of   Francis .  In the 16th century the two spellings were used indiscriminately for both sexes, the distinction in spelling not being established until the 17th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Frances Hughes was born in 1464, in Horsmonden, Kent, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir John Hughes. She died about 1524, in her hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1464–Abt 1524":"1464–umbes 1524","1464–1543":"1464–1543","1507–1577":"1507–1577","1464–1524":"1464–1524","1524":"1524","1577":"1577","1543":"1543","1464":"1464","Abt 1524":"umbes 1524","1507":"1507","Horsmonden, Tunbridge Wells district, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Horsmonden, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Horsmonden, Kent, England":"Horsmonden, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1464–Abt 1524":"1464–noin 1524","1464–154